==Starting out==
===Talking to the Strange Old Man===
* '''Strange Old Man:''' It's time.
* '''Player:''' Time for what?
* '''Strange Old Man:''' Time to dig. To dig, dig, dig. But no normal dig. We now have new purpose!
* '''Player:''' What do you mean? What purpose?
* '''Strange Old Man:''' The brothers six! Dutiful servants of Saradomin... At least, that's what they'd tell you! Ha! Not so. Not so.
* '''Strange Old Man:''' They made a pact you see! Strength in life for servitude in death.
* '''Player:''' Servitude?
* '''Strange Old Man:''' Yes! They guard it for him! That was their purpose, but that time is up now. He wants it back! You can get it! You can dig!
* '''Player:''' You want me to bring you something?
* '''Strange Old Man:''' The icon! He needs it now! You must dig, dig, dig. Slay the brothers six! It's okay, it won't hurt them... much. The icon will be in the chest!
* '''Player:''' Right... So you want me to go and kill the six brothers and bring you back an icon?
* '''Strange Old Man:''' Yes! Do this! Do this! Maybe little prize for you if you do. But first you must dig! Dig, dig, dig!
* '''Player:''' Okay...
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Can you tell me more about the brothers?}}
** '''Player:''' Can you tell me more about the brothers?
** {{tcond|If the player does not have the [[crumbling tome]] in their inventory:}}
*** '''Strange Old Man:''' The brothers? His faithful servants! Book tell you more! Take it! I don't even want it!
*** {{tbox|pic=Crumbling tome detail.png|The Strange Old Man gives you a book.}}
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player has the crumbling tome in their inventory:}}
*** '''Strange Old Man:''' The brothers? His faithful servants! Book tell you more! Read it! Read it!
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I wanted to ask you about warnings.}}
** '''Player:''' I wanted to ask you about warnings.
** '''Strange Old Man:''' Yes?
** {{tact|If the warnings are not combined:}}
*** '''Player:''' Currently when I'm trying to go plundering the catacombs here, my mind is plagued by several inconvenient warnings about the dangers below.
*** '''Player:''' I was wondering, do you know of a way to condense these warnings into a single one?
*** {{tact|continue}}
** {{tact|If the warnings are combined:}}
*** '''Player:''' Thanks for having those mental warnings I was having condensed into a single one, but I miss having them seperated.
*** '''Player:''' Is there any chance you'd be willing to change it back for me?
*** {{tact|continue}}
** '''Strange Old Man:''' AAAAAAAAARRRRRRGGGGGHHHHHHHH!
** '''Player:''' I'm guessing that was a yes? In that case, thanks.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'll be back soon.}}
** '''Player:''' I'll be back soon.
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to him again without the icon===
* '''Strange Old Man:''' Icon?
* '''Player:''' I don't have it yet.
* '''Strange Old Man:''' Slow! No slow! Only fast! Fast dig! Dig, dig, dig!
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Can you tell me more about the brothers?}}
** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|I wanted to ask you about warnings.}}
** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|Okay, I'll be back soon.}}
** '''Player:''' Okay, I'll be back soon.
** {{tact|end}}

==Giving the strange icon==
* '''Strange Old Man:''' Icon?
* '''Player:''' Yes, I have it here.
* '''Strange Old Man:''' At last! Quick! Give it!
* {{tbox|pic=Strange icon detail.png|You give the icon to the Strange Old Man.}}
* {{anchor|given-the-icon}}'''Strange Old Man:''' You did it! Now for me.
* {{tbox|pic=28131 detail.png|Before you can react, the Strange Old Man casts a spell. The icon disintegrates in his hands.}}
* '''Strange Old Man:''' It's all little bits now.
* '''Player:''' What? But why? I thought you needed it!
* {{anchor|destroyed-the-icon}}'''Strange Old Man:''' Yes! Needed it for him, but not to keep! His friend asked him to protect it, but he made a new plan, a better plan!
* '''Player:''' What are you on about?
* '''Strange Old Man:''' The old plan is gone. We're not doing it that way. His friend won't be happy, but it was for the best!
* '''Strange Old Man:''' Now we're doing it his way...
* '''Strange Old Man:''' Anyway, job well done! Still more digging though. Always dig. Dig, dig, dig!
* '''Strange Old Man:''' Oh, and don't forget your prize! He made it very clear you had to have a prize!
* {{tbox|pic=Dusty lamp detail.png|pic2=Crypt map detail.png|The Strange Old Man gives you a lamp and a map.}}
* '''Player:''' Thanks... I guess.
* {{tact|end}}

===If the player gives the strange old man the icon===
* {{tact|above|given-the-icon}}

===If the strange old man destroyed the icon===
* '''Player:''' Why did you destroy the icon? I though you needed it!
* {{tact|above|destroyed-the-icon}}

===If the player claims the lamp or map later===
* '''Strange Old Man:''' This is for you. Take it! Take it!
* {{tcond|If the player has not claimed the lamp nor the map:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Dusty lamp detail.png|pic2=Crypt map detail.png|The Strange Old Man has given you a lamp and a map.}}
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player has not claimed the lamp:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Dusty lamp detail.png|The Strange Old Man has given you a lamp.}}
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player has not claimed the map:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Crypt map detail.png|The Strange Old Man has given you a map.}}
** {{tact|continues}}
* '''Player:''' Thanks. 
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Can you tell me more about the brothers?}}
** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|I wanted to ask you about warnings.}}
** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|I'll leave you to it then...}}
** '''Player:''' I'll leave you to it then...
** {{tact|end}}

